{"title_page": "United States at the Winter Olympics", "text_new": "{{Main|United States at the Olympics}}\n{{Infobox country at games\n| NOC = USA\n| NOCname = [[United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee]]\n| games = Olympics\n| year = \n| flagcaption = [[Flag of the United States]]\n| oldcode = \n| website = \n| location = \n| competitors = \n| sports = \n| flagbearer = \n| rank = 2\n| gold = 105\n| silver = 112\n| bronze = 88\n| officials = \n| appearances = \n| app_begin_year = \n| app_end_year = \n| winterappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=United States|competition=Winter Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }}\n}}\nThe '''[[United States|United States of America]]''' has sent athletes to every celebration of the [[Winter Olympic Games]]. The [[United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee]] (USOPC) is the [[National Olympic Committee]] for the United States.\n\n== Hosted Games ==\nThe United States has hosted the Winter Games on '''four''' occasions, more than any other nation:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Games !! Host city !! Dates !! Nations !! Participants !! Events \n|-\n|[[1932 Winter Olympics]] || [[Lake Placid, New York|Lake Placid]], [[New York (state)|New York]] || February 7\u201315 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 17 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 252 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 14\n|-\n|[[1960 Winter Olympics]] || [[Squaw Valley Ski Resort|Squaw Valley]], [[California]] || February 2\u201320 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 30 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 665 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 27\n|-\n|[[1980 Winter Olympics]] || [[Lake Placid, New York]] || February 13\u201324 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 37 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1,072 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 38\n|-\n|[[2002 Winter Olympics]] || [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]] || February 8\u201324 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 77 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2,399 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 78\n|}\n\n== Medal tables ==\n{{See also|All-time Olympic Games medal count}}\n:''Red border color indicates host nation status.''\n\n=== Medals by Winter Games ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!Games\n!Athletes\n|style=\"background:gold; width:3.2em; font-weight:bold;\"|Gold\n|style=\"background:silver; width:3.7em; font-weight:bold;\"|Silver\n|style=\"background:#c96; width:3.7em; font-weight:bold;\"|Bronze\n!style=\"width:3.5em; font-weight:bold;\"|Total\n!style=\"width:4em; font-weight:bold;\"|[[Olympic medal table|Gold medals]]\n!style=\"width:4em; font-weight:bold;\"|[[Olympic medal table|Total medals]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1924}} || 24 || 1 || 2 || 1 || '''4''' || [[1924 Winter Olympics medal table|5]] || style=\"background:#ffdab9;\"|[[1924 Winter Olympics medal table|3]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1928}} || 24 || 2 || 2 || 2 || '''6''' || style=\"background:#dce5e5;\"|[[1928 Winter Olympics medal table|2]] || style=\"background:#dce5e5;\"|[[1928 Winter Olympics medal table|2]]\n|- style=\"border: 3px solid red\"\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1932}} || 64 || 6 || 4 || 2 || '''12''' || style=\"background:#f7f6a8;\"|[[1932 Winter Olympics medal table|1]] || style=\"background:#f7f6a8;\"|[[1932 Winter Olympics medal table|1]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1936}} || 55 || 1 || 0 || 3 || '''4''' || [[1936 Winter Olympics medal table|8]] || [[1936 Winter Olympics medal table|6]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1948}} || 69 || 3 || 4 || 2 || '''9''' || [[1948 Winter Olympics medal table|4]] || [[1948 Winter Olympics medal table|4]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1952}} || 65 || 4 || 6 || 1 || '''11''' || style=\"background:#dce5e5;\"|[[1952 Winter Olympics medal table|2]] || style=\"background:#dce5e5;\"|[[1952 Winter Olympics medal table|2]]\n|-\n|align=left| {{GamesName|WOG|1956}} || 67 || 2 || 3 || 2 || '''7''' || [[1956 Winter Olympics medal table|6]] || [[1956 Winter Olympics medal table|5]]\n|- style=\"border: 3px solid red\"\n|ali